Had the most epic time with our good friend Spencer Kane (@spencerkanemusic) on this week’s episode of The Dreamos Podcast! If you don’t know Spencer yet, he’s an incredible human and insanely gifted music artist getting after his dreams from Nashville, TN. ⁣
⁣
Starting his career off at a young age, Spencer’s gone through every high and low you can imagine. With faith locked in and the hustle to back up what he believes, Spencer infuses all he’s been through into the music he creates. In our convo, Spencer shares what it’s been like navigating a rapidly changing industry, the value of authenticity, how to take chances, and encouraging us all to do our thing. ⁣
⁣
We know you’ll be encouraged as you hear more from Spencer’s story, pursuit, and perspective.⁣
⁣
Link in bio for ways to listen.⁣

It’s been 6 years with you. I can’t believe all the places we’ve seen together and all the things we’ve conquered. We are definitely not the people we were when we first got together. We have grown up together, we have changed together, we have journeyed together, and cried together. I can’t wait to see who we will be in another 6 years, and I can’t wait to look back and laugh at the people we were “once upon a time”. Whoever you turn out to be, I’m excited to learn about him and love him.
Wifey and I made it 6 years together today.. 🥹 she’s my favorite muse, and my favorite girl. Love you B. @justbrookekane 🤞🏻

Some exciting news with @anthemlightsband, we started a Kickstarter for our brand new original album! I know, we rarely do original music, BUT we’ve been writing songs and figuring out what that would look like for a few years now, and we’re pumped to deliver a great record, FROM US. If you feel so inclined, click the link in my bio to check out the Kickstarter and see if you’d like to be involved. We already have one of the songs on radio right now (swipe right), so go request it at your local Christian radio station! S/o to the early believers in the record - KCMS Seattle, KXOJ Tulsa, WPOZ Orlando, 106.9 Spring Arbor, MI, and to the stations picking it up each day 🖤 officially my first top 40 song ever 🥹

Yesterday was Indigenous Peoples’ Day. A day to reflect and recognize the many horrors Native people have had to endure, and to celebrate the beautiful communities that remain and are fighting for their rights and lands to this day. I’ve been blessed to marry this beautiful woman and learn about her family, extended family, ancestors, etc and I couldn’t be prouder to stand along side you. Im so proud of who you are, what you stand for, and the woman you desire to be for your community, and one day, our children. I’m thankful to be in a country that’s allowed us freedom and opportunity, but to be aware of our nations true history so we can improve our future, is necessary. 🖤 I love you @justbrookekane
